theorem interior_frontier_eq_empty_of_open
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    interior (frontier (A : Set X)) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    -- Obtain an open neighbourhood `U` of `x` contained in the frontier.
    rcases (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).1 hx with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsub⟩
    -- Every point of `U` lies in `closure A`.
    have hU_closure : (U : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      intro y hyU
      exact
        (frontier_subset_closure (X := X) (A := A)) (hUsub hyU)
    -- Hence `x` itself belongs to `closure A`.
    have hx_closure : x ∈ closure A := hU_closure hxU
    -- The neighbourhood `U` must intersect `A`.
    have h_nonempty : ((U : Set X) ∩ A).Nonempty := by
      have h := (mem_closure_iff).1 hx_closure
      exact h U hUopen hxU
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, hyU, hyA⟩
    -- But `U ⊆ frontier A`, so `y ∉ A` since `A` is open.
    have hy_notA : y ∉ A := by
      have hFront : y ∈ frontier A := hUsub hyU
      have hNotInt : y ∉ interior A := hFront.2
      simpa [hA.interior_eq] using hNotInt
    -- Contradiction, hence the interior is empty.
    simpa using (hy_notA hyA)
  · exact Set.empty_subset _

theorem frontier_inter_subset_closure_pair
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    frontier (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ closure A ∩ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  -- From `hx` we obtain membership in `closure (A ∩ B)`.
  have hx_cl : x ∈ closure (A ∩ B) := hx.1
  -- `closure (A ∩ B)` is contained in each of `closure A` and `closure B`.
  have hA : closure (A ∩ B) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A)
  have hB : closure (A ∩ B) ⊆ closure B :=
    closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)
  exact And.intro (hA hx_cl) (hB hx_cl)
